tep 4 but with the following centrifuge conditions: <\/div><div class = \"text-block\"> .<\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"40F372B0FFA311EA992C4B333BFD1786","order_id":2,"type_id":30,"title":"centrifuge","source":{"centrifuge":"270","duration":300,"guid":"40F372B0FFA311EA992C4B333BFD1786","id":0,"label":"","pause":null,"preset":[],"start":null,"temperature":"20","temperatureUnit":10,"unit":1324}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1039803,"guid":"5069BB00FFA311EA992C4B333BFD1786","previous_id":1039802,"previous_guid":"289AFEE0FFA311EA992C4B333BFD1786","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"2B376EE94AED4B69B64FC44A233960FE","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"DBF5FF05FCA64047A313A4D281DCC74D","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Remove supernatant, add <\/div><div class = \"text-block\"> of PBS, and pipette vigorously.<\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"61DA6C90FFCB11EAB6B5FF9F3A665B98","order_id":2,"type_id":3,"title":"amount","source":{"amount":2,"unit":"mL","title":""}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1039804,"guid":"76E0FD70FFA311EA992C4B333BFD1786","previous_id":1039803,"previous_guid":"5069BB00FFA311EA992C4B333BFD1786","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"A0881902FA4745C48542B3202A3C9106","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"9DA3438DD91B49EDB60D24F940A73194","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Prepare <\/div><div class = \"text-block\"> of Nycodenz at 17% with iohexol buffer in a 15 ml conical-bottom tube and slowly add the <\/div><div class = \"text-block\"> of ookinetes-PBS on the iohexol cushion.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Avoid mixing the two solutions.<\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"66F3D040FFCB11EAB6B5FF9F3A665B98","order_id":2,"type_id":3,"title":"amount","source":{"amount":5,"unit":"mL","title":""}},{"id":1054726,"guid":"6C0D33F0FFCB11EAB6B5FF9F3A665B98","order_id":3,"type_id":3,"title":"amount","source":{"amount":2,"unit":"mL","title":""}},{"id":1054727,"guid":"C56BA620FFA311EA992C4B333BFD1786","order_id":4,"type_id":30,"title":"centrifuge","source":{"centrifuge":"895","duration":900,"guid":"C56BA620FFA311EA992C4B333BFD1786","id":0,"label":"","pause":null,"preset":[],"start":null,"temperature":"20","temperatureUnit":10,"unit":1324}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1039848,"guid":"D22DA3E0FFA311EA992C4B333BFD1786","previous_id":1039804,"previous_guid":"76E0FD70FFA311EA992C4B333BFD1786","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"EB083C1A8CF2483EB99AF2F9A93ED813","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"B95379E5B988481F91B128C7ED2852AE","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">Remove the brownish interphase between the PBS and the iohexol that contains the purified ookinetes.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Transfer the interphase to a 15 ml conical-bottom and add <\/div><div class = \"text-block\"> of PBS.<\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"732C0490FFCB11EAB6B5FF9F3A665B98","order_id":2,"type_id":3,"title":"amount","source":{"amount":10,"unit":"mL","title":""}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id":1039892,"guid":"0E698FE0FFA411EA992C4B333BFD1786","previous_id":1039848,"previous_guid":"D22DA3E0FFA311EA992C4B333BFD1786","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"F52087947A3943EFA30CE4B2071A3357","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":""}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"15EB72B6B60A440CBD4424349268D4DF","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"> to remove the Nycodenz. Repeat two times.<\/div><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"FB05C440FFA411EA992C4B333BFD1786","order_id":2,"type_id":30,"title":"centrifuge","source":{"centrifuge":"270","duration":300,"guid":"FB05C440FFA411EA992C4B333BFD1786","id":0,"label":"","pause":null,"preset":[],"start":null,"temperature":"20","temperatureUnit":10,"unit":1324}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"","section_duration":0,"critical":null,"critical_id":null,"duration":0}],"document":null,"materials":[],"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\">The ookinetes, as they come from the ookinete culture, are suspended in a solution that also contains blood cells and other parasite stages. Often, it is necessary to purify the ookinetes from these other cell types. This is achieved exploiting biological, chemical, and physical properties of the ookinetes that differ from the other cell types present in the ookinete culture.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><span>This protocol first exploits the ookinete's biological property of laking a Cl<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:super;\">-<\/span><span>\/HCO<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:sub;vertical-align:sub;\">3<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:sub;vertical-align:sub;\">-<\/span><span> channel in the membrane. On the contrary, the red blood cells (RBC) do have this channel. Because of this, RBC can be selectively lysed using an isotonic solution of NH<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:sub;\">4<\/span><span>Cl. In solution NH<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:sub;\">4<\/span><span>Cl dissociates into NH<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:super;vertical-align:sub;\">4<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:super;vertical-align:sub;\">+<\/span><span> and Cl<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:sub;\">-<\/span><span>, the NH<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:sub;vertical-align:sub;\">4<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:sub;vertical-align:sub;\">+<\/span><span> then transforms into NH<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:super;\">3<\/span><span>, which is permeable to the plasma membrane in contrast to the NH<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:super;vertical-align:sub;\">4<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:super;vertical-align:sub;\">+<\/span><span>. Once inside the cell, NH<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:super;\">3<\/span><span> establishes an equilibrium with NH<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:super;vertical-align:sub;\">4<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:super;vertical-align:sub;\">+<\/span><span> resulting in a net influx of Cl<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:sub;\">-<\/span><span> through the aforementioned ion channel, increasing the NH<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:super;\">4<\/span><span>Cl concentration in the RBC considerably and, therefore, of water, causing an osmotic shock and RBC burst. Since HCO<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:super;vertical-align:sub;\">3<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:super;vertical-align:sub;\">-<\/span><span> is in equilibrium with CO<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:super;\">2<\/span><span>, RBC lysis must be performed during shaking to increase the concentration of CO<\/span><span style = \"vertical-align:sub;\">2<\/span><span> in the solution (Chernyshev, et al., 2007).<\/span><\/div><div class = \"text-block\">Next a series of differential centrifugations are performed exploiting the sedimentation rate of the ookinetes, which depends on the size, shape, and density of the ookinetes as well as on the viscosity of the medium. The last step involves isopycnic centrifugation in a density cushion taking advantage of the buoyant density of the ookinetes.<\/div><div class = \"text-block\">This method has been modified from Rodr\u00edguez M.C., et al., 2002 and Carter V., et al., 2003.<\/div><\/div>","changed_on":1605745422}